# Copy this file to .env.local (or .env) and fill in only what you need.
# Nothing here is required for local development — `npm run dev` works with
# none of these set, exactly as before this file existed.

# Origin of the separate, standalone Battle Map VTT app (a different
# project), used only for the "open in external VTT" fallback link when a
# battle entry has no in-app battle map configured. This app's own embedded
# battle overlay is the primary way to run combat and never needs this.
# Leave unset on a server deployment unless you actually run that other app
# somewhere reachable — an unset value now correctly shows "Боевая карта не
# настроена" instead of linking to a dead localhost address.
# VITE_BATTLE_MAP_VTT_ORIGIN=http://localhost:4174

# Base URL of this campaign app's own future backend API (see
# docs/SERVER_ROADMAP.md). Not used by anything yet — every save/load goes
# through the localStorage adapter in src/state/persistence/overlayStorage.ts.
# Reserved so a network-backed persistence adapter has one obvious place to
# read its endpoint from once it exists.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-server.example.com/api
